Wilshire Grand Center is a skyscraper in the Financial District of Downtown Los Angeles , California .
It is the tallest building in Los Angeles , the tallest building in California , the tallest building west of the Mississippi River and outside of New York City , Chicago , and Philadelphia , and the 11th tallest building in the United States .
Its height surpasses the U.S. Bank Tower by .
The building is part of a mixed - use hotel , retail , observation decks , shopping mall , and office complex , expected to revitalize downtown Los Angeles and the area surrounding the building .
The development of the complex is estimated to cost $ 1.2 billion .
The plans include of retail , of Class A office space and 900 hotel rooms .
InterContinental is the tower 's hotel component , comprising 900 rooms and suites .
